fields.name: BracesMatch
fields.description: Nothing should be left open. Please, close all.

fields.name: DesreverSort
fields.description: Dr Desrever wants to sort these words so that last letters are sorted. e.g. 'start' is after 'end' since 't' is after 'd' e.g. 'tonight' is after 'highlight' since 'thgin' is after 'thgil'

fields.name: Difference
fields.description: The difference is the key. e.g. ru: 00; rv: 00

fields.name: DifferenceEviler
fields.description: The difference is the key but one of these values is bad, which one ? e.g. u: 47583;v: 64829

fields.name: DifferenceUnknown
fields.description: One of these values is bad, which one? e.g. 42

fields.name: JustHexa
fields.description: Please translate what is inside quotes into hexadecimal notation (using ASCII table, two digit with uppercase letters) e.g. This is "a" sentence with some "quoted" text => 6171756F746564

fields.name: JustHexaEvil
fields.description: Please translate what is inside quotes into hexadecimal notation (using ASCII table, two digit with uppercase letters) e.g. This is "a" sentence with some "quoted" text => 6171756F746564

fields.name: LostInMaze
fields.description: robot is lost in a radioactive complex. It undestands cardinal directions: n (for noth), s (for south), e (for east) and w (for west) When it would hit a wall it stays in place, silently. Also, when it is out of the complex, it cannot enter again.

fields.name: MrReverse
fields.description: Mr Esrever like to read his poems in reverse. Please, translate.

fields.name: RomanProblems
fields.description: Please, help Nero's scribe. He's bad at computing.

fields.name: ThreeBigs
fields.description: Find all one lowercase surronded by exactly three uppercase and write them packed.

fields.name: ThreeBigsEviler
fields.description: Find all one lowercase surronded by exactly three uppercase and write them packed.

fields.name: TinyOverflow
fields.description: A simple multiplication. Just give the right answer.

fields.name: TokenByPairs
fields.description: Delete the pairs to find the unmatched word.
